id: resume-workflow
version: 1.0.0
problem: The user wants to continue a workflow that was previously started.
recognition[6]: Resume workflow,Continue workflow,Restart workflow,Pick up where I left off,Continue the work-package,Where were we?
skills:
  primary: workflow-execution
  supporting[0]:
outcome[4]: Previous state is restored or reconstructed,Current phase is identified,Remaining work is presented,Agent is ready to continue guiding user
flow[12]: 1. Ask user to identify the workflow being resumed,2. Call get_workflow to load workflow definition,"3. Reconstruct state by asking user:","   - Which phase were you on?","   - What phases have been completed?","   - Any key decisions already made?",4. Call get_phase for current phase,"5. Present current phase status:","   - Completed steps (if any)","   - Remaining steps","   - Upcoming checkpoints",6. Resume execution from current position
context_to_preserve[5]: workflowId - The workflow being resumed,currentPhase - Phase to resume from,completedPhases - Phases already completed,checkpointResponses - Previous user decisions,variables - Current variable values